name: IterableZip
comment:
Iterable that iterates over lists of values from other iterables.

When collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.iterator is read, an collection/dart-core.Iterator is created for each collection/dart-core.Iterable in the collection/dart-core.Iterable passed to the constructor.

As long as all these iterators have a next value, those next values are combined into a single list, which becomes the next value of this collection/dart-core.Iterable's collection/dart-core.Iterator. As soon as any of the iterators run out, the zipped iterator also stops.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an iterator that combines values of the iterables' iterators as long as they all have values.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in this.

Counting all elements may be involve running through all elements and can therefore be slow.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate test. Returns false otherwise.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.contains.element.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.elementAt.indexth element.

The collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.elementAt.index elements in this.

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate test. Returns false otherwise.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.join.separator string.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.map.f multiple times on the same element.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.skipWhile.test.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.take.n elements.

It is an error if collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if collection/dart-pkg-collection-iterable_zip.IterableZip.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment:
Returns a string representation of (some of) the elements of this.

Elements are represented by their own toString results.

The representation always contains the first three elements. If there are less than a hundred elements in the iterable, it also contains the last two elements.

If the resulting string isn't above 80 characters, more elements are included from the start of the iterable.

The conversion may omit calling toString on some elements if they are known to now occur in the output, and it may stop iterating after a hundred elements.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function test multiple times on the same element.
